records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tyler J Lewein in court with attorney Kelsey Loshaw.  Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court vacates previous plea.  State files Amended Information.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Court conducts plea colloquy with defendant.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation. Defendant makes statement.  

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 MONTHS JAIL (CREDIT - 3 days)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s; 
*Comply with Drug Treatment Court after-care;
*Attend one self-help meeting per week;
*Attend one Drug Treatment Court alumni meeting per month;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Upon agent's approval defendant may petition for early termination of probation after 6 months.
